## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, or Edge)
- Basic understanding of web servers

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/imabutahersiddik/connecthub.git
cd connecthub
```

2. Project Structure:
```
connecthub/
├── assets/
│   └── logo.svg
├── screenshots/
│   ├── dashboard.png
│   ├── calendar.png
│   ├── documents.png
│   └── team.png
├── index.html
├── styles.css
├── script.js
└── README.md
```

3. Start a local server:

Using Python:
```bash
python -m http.server 8000
```

Using Node.js:
```bash
npx serve
```

4. Access the dashboard:
- Open your browser
- Navigate to `http://localhost:8000`

## 💻 Usage

### Navigation
- Use the top navigation bar for main sections
- Side menu for quick access to resources
- Quick actions available on the dashboard

### User Profile
- Click the profile icon to access settings
- Manage notifications through the bell icon
- View real-time updates in UTC (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS format)

### Calendar
- Navigate between months
- Click on dates to view events
- Add new events using the "+" button

### Documents
- Browse categories in the sidebar
- Upload files using drag-and-drop
- Quick actions for download and sharing

